(205, 2, 25, 'HBS Admissions Liaison\nHarvard University Candidate interviewer\nLiberal Arts Education - same as the Ivies.\nFormer Ed Finance Executive.\n\nWill review in context of aiming of understand the person as individual - looking for personal connection in the essay in conjunction with other elements of the application. The whole thing must hang together.', 1, NULL, 0, '2016-02-09 19:02:21', NULL),
(237, 1, 25, 'Experience with preparing for college and grad school in engineering - from school tutoring, to PSAT and SATs,  addressing concerns with grades in your essays, and deciding to go to grad school (GRE, GMAT related questions also). ', 1, NULL, 0, '2016-02-05 14:23:45', NULL),
(206, 1, 15, 'Happy to provide guidance on overall themes- elements missing or those which should be elaborated upon/ de-emphasized. Also basic edits and guidance on language.', 1, NULL, 0, '2016-01-19 16:03:38', 'abhinav.sharman@gmail.com'),
(209, 1, 75, 'I have a love for language, spending great time in honing my ability to crisply present complex ideas. My work began as an undergraduate student at Brown University, where I eventually assumed the positions of Editor for Brown University''s Policy Review and a Peace Corps Newsletter. Later, as a student at Michigan Law, I began honing my storytelling craft, developing a narrative flair that I now use in engaging the reader in any topic, ranging from academic topics to more creative works. I continue to write blogposts and articles in the areas of Public Policy and Higher Education, which can be found on my LinkedIn profile.', 1, NULL, 0, '2016-01-25 23:22:09', NULL),
(81, 1, 100, 'I''m a Stanford graduate and have also been a Teaching Assistant during my graduate study at Stanford. I also work as a part-time educational consultant and aid students in their college admission process. I''ve edited and proofread numerous application for college applications. \n\nApart from reviewing the essays for grammatical errors, spelling mistakes and structured English, I ensure that the essay is well-built and highly personalized.  I am familiar with the nuances of the college application process, and I also understand what admissions committees are looking for in these essays.    \n\n', 0, NULL, 0, '2016-01-19 15:16:05', 'akira@gmail.com');

